# Function documentation (English only)

For **all new and edited code** in this repository, **every function must be explained in English** before or above its definition.

Works together with `english-comments-and-logs.mdc`: explanations, JSDoc, and inline comments are **English only**.

## What must be documented

- Named functions and `async` functions
- `const` / `function` helpers at module or class scope
- Class methods and React hooks (`useXxx`)
- Exported APIs (content scripts, background, popup, `sites/`, download core)

## What to write

Use **JSDoc** when possible. At minimum, one English sentence stating **what the function does** and **why** (if non-obvious).

Add `@param` / `@returns` when parameters or return value are not self-explanatory from names and types.

```ts
/**
 * Extract direct http(s) mp4/m3u8/webm URLs from <video> elements on the page.
 * Used as a fallback when no site-specific sniffer is registered or returns empty.
 */
export function extractDirectVideoTagUrls(): SiteVideoInfo[] {
  // ...
}

/**
 * Wait until DOM is parsed; content scripts may run at document_start.
 */
export function waitForDomReady(): Promise<void> {
  // ...
}
```

## Exceptions (still prefer a one-line English comment if unclear)

- Trivial inline callbacks in `.map` / `.filter` / `.forEach` (single expression, obvious intent)
- Auto-generated or third-party vendored files (do not rewrite wholesale)

## Avoid

```ts
// ❌ No explanation
export function resolveSiteVideoUrls(topDomain: string, hostMap: HostGetUrlsMap) {
  // ...
}

// ❌ Non-English explanation
/** [extract m3u8 from video tags — use English instead] */
function extract() {}

// ✅ English JSDoc
/** Resolve video URLs: site-specific sniffer first, then generic <video> direct links. */
function resolveSiteVideoUrls(topDomain: string, hostMap: HostGetUrlsMap) {}
```

When editing a file, add English docs to **new functions** and to **existing functions you touch** if they lack documentation.
